A Krugersdorp man is in a serious condition after being shot during a suspected armed robbery at his home in Mindalore on Friday night. Netcare 911 spokesman Shawn Herbst said paramedics had responded to reports of a shooting at the house at 9.54pm on Friday evening. “Reports from the scene indicate that an adult male sustained two gun shot wounds in a suspected armed robbery. “The patient was treated on scene by an advanced life support paramedic and transported by ambulance in a serious condition to hospital for further treatment‚” Herbst added.